column6: Dayssi Olarte de Kanavos is a hotelier and urban real estate developer based out of New York City. She is the co-founder, President and COO of Flag Luxury Group LLC. Flag Luxury is a real estate development company with a primary focus on luxury hotels, boutique hotels and retail development. In her role as President, Olarte de Kanavos is involved in all aspects of Flag Luxury’s real estate initiatives which include site selection, finance and acquisitions, selection of hotel brands, management contracts, architectural and interior design, hotel properties programming, zoning and construction, and asset management. Prior to joining the Flag Group of Companies, Olarte de Kanavos completed a Masters in Real Estate Development and Finance from New York University after several years working in New York as a commercial real estate financial analyst and broker. She received a Bachelor of a Science from the School of Hotel Administration from Cornell University. Olarte de Kanavos is a member of The School of Hotel Administration Dean’s Advisory Board at Cornell University. She also serves on the Cornell University Council; The President's Council of Cornell Women; Major Gifts Campaign committee member. She was the guest lecturer in the 45th edition of the Dean’s Distinguished Lecture Series at the School of Hotel Administration. She is also the Founder of The Friends Of New Yorkers For Children which support children in foster care through initiatives in education, mentoring, and career opportunities.

Born the 29 .10. 1988 (scorpion & dragon) in Nice cote d'azure "France" I come from a long legacy of architects with 4 generations of interior designer, a proud member of the Meniaud family name. My great grand father was a upholsterer and designer in Egypt while, my grand father Jean-Yves Meniaud was the interior designer for the firm Jensen Paris spanning a long career. My father Guillaume Meniaud, an award winning interior designer on his work with project like One Sandy Lane, Palazzate… Further inspired me to continue the family tradition in designing. I graduated from the Nice Architectural School ITcomdesign in 2009. During my tenure at architectural school i had the opportunity of working for a prestigious firm with a world class reputation like MG design (Beaulieu sur mer - france) & Architects associates (St.jean cap ferret - France). There I gain valuable knowledge and work experience while applying the skills taught to me at school with the real world application of architecture. In 2010 i moved to St.Barth where i had the chance of working for the company DESIGN AFFAIRS, where i had the great opportunity to work on various types of projects inclusive of hotels, restaurants, private properties and apartments. This experience broadened my knowledge base as well as my flexibility as an architect to transform not only the largest but also the smallest places into a piece or art with functional design. End of 2012 i decided to move to BARBADOS primarily to work with my father GUILLAUME MENIAUD & the firm CIDesign where i had the pleasure of working on projects geared towards more luxury designs. I am always looking fora new project and challenge. I currently manage my own projects with the same professionalism, dedication and designing eye taught to me from not only my education and work experience but also with a keen sense of design inherited from a rich history of designing entrepreneurs.

column6: After graduating from the University of Delaware in 1981, David worked for several flooring companies. With this knowledge and the knowledge he gained from his father who was also in the flooring business; he joined BASF Fibers, the originator of solution dyed products, as a Contract Carpet Consultant in 1984. From there he became Regional Manager for Lotus Carpets, Commercial Dealer Rep for Lasher Carpet and VP for Corporate Carpet Systems. After learning everything he could about the industry, he decided it was time to start his own business and opened the doors of Concorde Flooring Systems which quickly became one of the New York area's premier independent commercial flooring dealers and consultants. During his tenure as President and CEO, he received numerous industry and business awards including the DuPont Antron award and INC. Magazine's award for one of the 500 fastest growing, privately held companies in the USA. Some ten years later, he realized that a smaller, boutique approach to the flooring industry would better fit new industry trends, as well as provide him the opportunity to bring more upscale, unique products to his clients. Given his understanding of what end-users and architects want and the ability to balance their wishes with what manufacturers can and do produce, he knew just what type of company was in order. And so, Summit International Flooring was born... Specialties: David has been successful because he knows flooring from the inside out and personally invests in suppliers that have UNIQUE products. He is constantly sourcing new products to provide his clients with the newest, most distinctive flooring options available; bringing these extraordinary flooring products to the USA and creating a market for them. Demand is generated based on his own experience and individual feel for a product.

She currently does provides consulting and as managing director, heads the firms Family Office Group.

 Pat also has extensive board service background. She was a member of the board of directors for Office Depot, Inc. and is currently the chair of the board of directors for the Florida Atlantic University Foundation. A member of the Audit Committee for Holy Cross Hospital, Pat also previously served as a member of the advisory board of Blueware Inc., an EMR health care technology company. She currently serves as a Trustee for the Washington, DC based Committee for Economic Development (CED), a public policy forum. Pat is the Vice Chairman and CFO of Women Corporate Directors, is also a member of its Global Advisory Board and co-chairs its South Florida chapter. She also serves on the Florida board of NACD. Pat serves as a member of the boards of various non-profit organizations.

 Pat has successfully executed complex transactions such as recapitalization strategies, acquisitions, divestitures, as well as the spin-offs. James Gregory Wilkinson is an award-winning travel editor and TV and radio commentator based in Sydney.For the last 16 years, James has been the Editor-In-Chief of the Asia-Pacific region’s highly respected hotel industry magazine, HM, and its online products.He is also the Travel Editor for Time Out Australia and Managing Editor of SPICE magazine and SpiceNews.Since late-2012, James has been a regular guest (appearing on over 105 episodes) on the Sky News Business Channel television show 'Business Class', where he commentates on trends in business travel, primarily aviation, hotels and destinations.James is also Chair of Laureate Australia Hospitality's Industry Advisory Board and Deputy Chair of the Young Garvan committee at the Garvan Research Foundation.In 2003, James co-founded the HM Awards (Australasia's largest hotel awards) and in 2010, the AHICE Conference, also the region's largest.He Chairs the Content Committee for AHICE and is the Chief Judge and co-organiser of the HM Awards.James has also been a guest on Channel 7's 'The Morning Show', radio 4BC in Brisbane and 3AW in Melbourne, and is formerly the Editor-In-Chief of Hilton, Australian Hotelier, Signature Cocktails and bars&clubs magazines. Prior to this, James was at Courier Newspapers.James was named 2008 Travel Writer of the Year for Trade / Industry by the Australian Society of Travel Writers, while in 2003, James received the received the Golden Circle Award from Marriott International. At the 2008 HM Awards, James screened a moving film (that he wrote, filmed, narrated, directed and produced) about the Sala Bai Hotel School in Cambodia. Following the documentary, over AUD$30,000 was raised for Sala Bai and over $200,000 since then. At the 2011 HM Awards, James helped raise $55,000 for the people of Christchurch.In 2010, James was a finalist for Travel Writer of the Year at the National Tourism Industry Awards (NTIAs), presented by the Australian Federation of Travel Agents.

Operating in an international market place and following the constant moving mega yacht industry drives Josh’s enthusiasm and level of success. Raised in Southern New England south of Boston, Josh's enthusiasm for boating started at a very early age and the passion for being on the water has been in his blood ever since. Upon the completion of his education at the New England Institute of Technology studying Marine Management, Josh began his career in yachting. Now having spent 26 years in the industry, Josh’s knowledge has great depth and very wide spread. The initial years were in building and service sector. Spending thirteen aboard private and charter yachts up to 150’ brought Josh through the Western Mediterranean, Western Atlantic, Caribbean Sea and the Eastern Pacific Ocean. These cruising and management experiences allow for Josh to thoroughly understand a clients needs pending the type of yachting they desire; be it light costal cruising or true global exploring. Josh’s real passion today is in the brokerage industry, constantly traveling internationally allowing him to be on top of the markets constant movement and personally visiting yachts both quietly for sale and others publically available. Being the catalyst for a deal and navigating the multiple layers in a transaction thrust Josh’s enthusiasm. Josh’s successes are directly contributed to his integrity, honesty and confidentiality clients at this level expect. J. David Armstrong, Jr. President Broward College J. David Armstrong, Jr. begins his 30th year of experience as a leader in higher education and economic development and his eighth year at Broward College serving Greater Fort Lauderdale. He leads one of the largest and most diverse colleges in America, enrolling more than 68,000 students from more than 185 different nations of origin, one-third born somewhere other than the U.S. Under President Armstrong, the college has grown from a traditional community college to an institution that also offers baccalaureate programs in targeted workforce areas, providing career opportunities for students and a trained workforce for business and industry. Broward College has been named one of the Top 10 colleges in America based on student success indicators by the Washington D.C. based Aspen Institute and continues to be consistently ranked in the top 5 producers of degrees nationally. His focus on expanding access to education, workforce development and global competitiveness has resulted in new locations, both locally and abroad, with 11 campuses and centers in Greater Fort Lauderdale and 10 international partnerships worldwide. President Armstrong has balanced the budget through efficiencies and growth -- reducing administrative costs per student while adding new programs such as manufacturing and new workforce bachelor’s degrees in Science, Math, Engineering and Technology (STEM) areas. Broward College has developed a new strategic plan focused on "Transforming Students' Lives by Connecting, Challenging and Completing." Broward has been awarded three national grants of more than $30 million to expand workforce programs including logistics, IT and manufacturing. He is Chairman of Leadership Florida, past chair of the Greater Ft Lauderdale Alliance, a member of the national Council on Competitiveness, and in 2013 participated in a Fulbright program to work with Russian government and higher education officials. Specialties: Leadership development, management coaching, organizational development, economic development, international education, and economic development, higher education policy

column6: College professor & Neuro-Education coach with over 20 years experience using evidence-based approaches to help educators boost student engagement, deepen learning & retention, and achieve mastery of tools proven to increase student outcomes. I have blended my extensive experience teaching dozens of courses to over 15,000 students from 95 countries with the latest research in effective teaching techniques to create the Training Transformational Teachers program. This program helps educators who want to become increasingly effective understand how learning really happens in the brain. It offers highly-focused and personalized training in brain-based routes to better learning and helps them experiment, over the course of a semester, with more effective ways to apply these routes to their individual classes and students. Though the training covers a lot of research on how the brain processes information best, the focus of the program is on helping each professor design, experiment with, and refine more effective teaching tools for their specific courses, and on tracking their effectiveness. You can find out all about how the program works here: tttprogram.com I also offer individual career coaching for self-directed professionals who are ready to transition to new, more challenging, and/or more meaningful opportunities. Using a carefully-designed sequence of evidence-based techniques, participants can identify, track, and embed the new habits that give them better professional and personal satisfaction with less effort. Here also, the focus is on using these new cognitive tools to help the client achieve professional goals their previous approaches haven't allowed them to reach. Specialties: I specialize in personalized applications of the evidence-based neuroscience of coaching to help clients reroute their thinking to more positive and productive career paths.

column6: Ricardo Dunin is a founding partner of Lionheart Capital, LLC (www.lheartcapital.com) and has over 30 years of experience in the Miami, Caribbean and Brazilian real estate markets.Lionheart Capital is a Miami-based global real estate investment and development firm whose principals have been involved with the successful acquisition, development, repositioning and disposition of real estate assets totaling over $4 billion in the United States, Brazil, China and the Caribbean. Projects include the Ritz Carlton Residences Palm Beach and the Ritz Carlton Residences Miami Beach.Prior to joining forces with OZ Holdings to found Lionheart Capital, Dunin was the CEO of the Flagler Group, Inc. Other high-profile Dunin projects include: The Meridian, an ultra-modern building of 111 luxury lofts in South Beach; Le Sereno, a beachfront resort designed by Parisian designer Christian Liaigre in St. Barth and the Miami Airport Center, a 640,000 square foot, mixed-use park adjacent to Miami International Airport.Dunin is also a founding partner of Performance Empreendimentos Imobiliarios, a Brazilian condo, office, and hotel development company, which is currently involved in over two billion dollars of development work in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil.Dunin is originally from Brazil and studied business at Fundaçao Getulio Vargas, the most prestigious business school in South America.

column6:
You could call me a social creature by nature. I’ve always had an insatiable hunger to meet new faces from all over the world. I started my career as a stockbroker, but realized before long that my passion and talent wasn’t in connecting dots, but connecting people. So it’s no wonder I ended up where I am today – a serial entrepreneur and the digital ‘go-to’ guy for the travel industry – fully immersed into an industry where personal experience and storytelling has been the key to my success.

 In today’s digital age, connecting people has become fairly easy. Forming meaningful, lasting business relationships – well, that’s the tough part. But 15 years of entrepreneurial experience has taught me (through much trial and error), how to manage people, their talents and strengths, and translate that into profitable businesses. The secret is, there’s no substitute for real life experience. So that’s why I’m here, to help by sharing my experiences and hopefully, foster opportunities where we can work together.

Trent'anni di storia, il prestigio del Maestro Lanzetta e di tutti i componenti ci consente di organizzare i concerti in location e musei unici al mondo come il Bargello, il Museo dell'Accademia e Piazza Signoria. Amo Firenze e vorrei con L'Orchestra da Camera Fiorentina regalare un nuovo modo di godere della musica Classica creando oltre che indimenticabili concerti, eventi ed occasioni di socializzazione.

Trisha believes in teamwork and partnerships that deliver exceptional results. Her passion for design and education is fuel for the leadership of her company Design Poole, an international award winning interior design firm. As a Florida native she received her Bachelors Degree in Interior Design from the University of Florida College of Architecture. Her active pace for success has not changed since being recognized at the young age of 32 as "40 Under 40 Rising Stars" by the Orlando Business Journal. After working as Design Director at Fugleburg Koch Architects and VP of Design at Gettys Group, she founded Design Poole Inc. in 2000. Design Poole has received multiple industry awards as Trisha maintains the ability to understand the Client's vision, articulate and drive design to a higher level with the respected and creative design team. Every project is approached as a blank canvas creating unique interior and outdoor living environments that speak to the demographic. "It is our job to balance the 'awe inspiring' with the practical side of design", Poole says. "The design team works on every project as a reliable resource to our clientele, in an effort to make their jobs easier. We want to leave a lasting impression with the guests of our hospitality spaces but also with our business partners when they review our performance and overall project success". Trisha is very active and "hands on" with affecting change and positive growth in the industry as she sits on advisory boards for international trade fairs, conferences and business development venues. Through decades of volunteer efforts with the non profit organization NEWH she strives to strengthen the industry by offering education to hospitality professionals and providing financial support to students in need through fundraising efforts. Building a strong foundation and credible talent pool to the hospitality businesses. Specialties: Interior Design, Graphic Design and Branding.

column6: Anthony (Tony) DePierro Tony’s rather diverse career began as he joined his families business, Medical Data Technology (MDT). MDT provided IT solutions to hospitals. MDT was sold to Alltel at which time Tony maintained an executive position. As Alltel sold this division off to Eclipsys, Tony went with the acquisition to Eclipsys to handle contractual negotiations for their legal department, which brought him to Delray Beach, Florida. In 2000, Tony had a vision to bring new life to Delray Beach. This birthed the rather famous restaurant called Sopra, which in Italian means “Above or to exceed”, Delray Beach has forever been changed for the better! Sopra was sold to BICE International Restaurant Group. Tony founded Sun Atlantic Properties (SAP), a commercial real estate company upon moving to Florida. One of the properties owned by SAP was Sopra Centre, which housed the famous Sopra Restaurant. SAP sold Sopra Centre for a record setting price per square foot. As a testament to Tony’s efforts the Sopra Centre and Sopra Restaurant have been memorialized in the history book of Delray Beach. Tony acquired the largest custom wheel company (Automotive) in the state of Florida called G Roads. G Roads carried over 500 wheel designs in house and catered to the rich and famous. During this time Tony also designed his own custom line of which he sold both in 2008. Tony has once again set his focus on commercial real estate. Most recently he has aligned himself with JSM Realty Services, wherein his business and entrepreneurial experience lends itself well to all aspects of commercial real estate with his primary focus in the Restaurant industry.

Mr. Bucaro brings 25 years of financial services expertise with a broad array of experience including product development and management, capital raising, fee income generation, and commercial real estate finance within world-class organizations, including the former First National Bank of Chicago (acquired by JP Morgan Chase) and ABN-AMRO North America (acquired by Bank of America). Mr. Bucaro’s current responsibilities include originating, underwriting, and financing commercial real estate assets. He has evaluated over $4 billion in financing opportunities across all properties types, including land, hotels, retail centers, apartment buildings, office and industrial properties, and has successfully closed individual transactions ranging from $5 million to over $150 million. Mr. Bucaro has experience structuring transactions at all levels of the capital stack, including senior mortgages, A/B structures, mezzanine debt, Historic and New Markets tax credit syndication, joint-venture equity, and fund-level equity investments. He is also responsible for establishing correspondent relationships with a wide range of capital sources, including hedge funds, life companies, investment banks, mortgage REITs, commercial banks, credit unions, and private money funds. Mr. Bucaro is a member of the Mortgage Bankers Association of America (MBA) and the International Council of Shopping Centers (ICSC), along with several local real estate organizations. Mr. Bucaro earned his MBA from DePaul University’s Kellstadt Graduate School of Business with a concentration in Commercial Real Estate Finance and Investment, and achieved a Certificate in Hotel Real Estate Investments and Asset Management from Cornell University's School of Hotel Administration

column6:
I have worked in media since I was 16. First in New Jersey as a writer for the Paterson News and the Record (now the Record). In Miami I was a DJ for WAEZ and converted country music station WBUS-FM and Love94 to progressive music formats under then owner Allen Margolis.

 In late 60's founded alternate culture magazine, the Daily Planet, Miami Beach, FL. After Nixon resigned I moved to NY. Somehow I landed up working with artists Andy Warhol, Peter Max and for a short time in Spain for Salvador Dali.

 In 1992 - I launched and created the luxe magazine Ocean Drive and 20 other titles including Ocean Drive in Spanish with partners Gloria and Emilio Estefan. In 1997 Michael Carr and I founded Vegas Magazine.

 Forward to 2007, sold company and between here and St. Bart's I returned to painting. October, 2014 a work of mine titled "Art Miami," was selected "Official Painting of Art Miami's 25th Anniversary" and so a new career began!

 Exhibits of my art included; Art Miami/Context; Art Wynwood; Art Miami, New York; Kavachnina Contemporary; The Jewish Museum, Miami Beach; Swampspace Gallery, Miami, Florida, and a stellar exhibition on Worth Avenue's, Arcature Fine Arts. And yes, I've actually sold some works on paper; two commissioned character portraits; and several multi media acrylic paintings from my "mugSHOT" series.

 I completed a series of new works. I've made a great connection with "found objects" from my Dad's closet. Its fun - but can get spooky at times. A few months ago we published and launched a new annual magazine called ART MIAMI. It was done with partners Art Miami, LLC. This coming year (2016) we will again produce a print and digital magazine celebrating "Art Week" in Miami. The December book will have a much wider range, but with no alliance to any particular fair - but will cover most art fairs, galleries and museums and private collections. For advertising details contact me at jerrypow@aol.com.

Rick Hess is a Silicon Valley entrepreneur, for-profit and non-profit executive living in the San Francisco Bay area. Rick is a graduate of Franklin & Marshall College, and attended George Washington University Graduate School of Business and Georgetown University. Rick started his career in Washington, D.C., working for Digital Equipment Corporation (now HP), and then joined Oracle Corporation in Silicon Valley in the mid-1980's and helped build the company. Rick was a director in strategic accounts and was then promoted to Managing Director/senior VP of East Asia, based in Hong Kong, responsible for all aspects of Oracle's business in the region. He later joined PeopleSoft (now Oracle) as VP International, and then Hyperion (now Oracle) as VP International and global channels. He returned to Oracle as a VP at corporate headquarters, responsible for a $200 Million+ annual business. In between senior positions at Oracle, Rick helped form, grow, and exit two start-ups, WebCare and Ellianz, serving as CEO of both companies. He also served as an Entrepreneur in Residence (EIR) at two Silicon Valley venture capital firms, Mohr Davidow Ventures and Allegis Capital. Rick is active in politics, serving on President Obama's Economic, Globalization, and Trade policy committee. Rick has served on the board of directors for multiple for-profits, 501(c)3 non-profits, and academic institutions.

Jason Binn founded DuJour Media in the summer of 2012. The publication is an innovative, multi-platform digital and print magazine utilizing targeted analytics to reach more than 3 million readers and users monthly across the country. DuJour targets the affluent market and chronicles the vibrant world of the wealthiest and most inspiring individuals. DuJour's strategic partner is Gilt Groupe, the online retailer where Jason Binn served as an advisor starting in 2010. In the fall of 2016, Jason Binn was appointed Chief Advisor to the board of directors while becoming an active shareholder to the worldwide nightlife and events booking app InList. InList curates the hottest events and venues nightly in over 45 cities. InList allows its members to book tables, get VIP access and purchase tickets to exclusive events with an in-app concierge at their fingertips. Prior to DuJour, Jason Binn founded Niche Media in 1992, a leading publisher of luxury regional magazines nationwide (Aspen Peak, Boston Common, Capitol File, Gotham, Hamptons, Los Angeles Confidential, Michigan Avenue, Ocean Drive, Philadelphia Style and Vegas). In addition, a custom publishing department was created under Niche Media, which created publications for Art Basel Miami Beach, Wynn Las Vegas and the Short Hills Mall for the Taubman real estate organization. In 2006, Binn sold Niche Media for an undisclosed sum to the Greenspun Media Group (GMG) continuing to serve as CEO. In 2007, GMG purchased the Ocean Drive Media Group, which Binn co-owned and founded. After the successful merger and transition, Binn continued to oversee the operations and management of the company until his resignation in 2010. Additionally, Binn is co-founder of the Binn Animal Rescue and Sanctuary Charitable Foundation, and a patron of God's Love We Deliver.
